Spectrum Brands Appoints Andreas Rouve as CEO
Succeeds Dave Lumley, who announced his plans to retire in January

 






By

Angela Chen



  March 16, 2015 7:26 a.m. ET





 Spectrum Brands Holdings Inc. has appointed Andreas Rouve as chief executive, succeeding Dave Lumley, who is retiring. Mr. Rouve, 53 years old, was most recently chief operating officer of the consumer goods company, whose diverse offerings of consumer products range from Rayovac batteries to George Foreman grills. He also held positions as president of the company’s international division, and senior vice president of the European...
  


